<HelpLayout title="Everything Badger does" description="A full map of Badger's features, one line each, so you can find an option you did not know existed and learn it in one click.">
  <h1>Everything Badger does</h1>
  <p>This is the full map. You will not need most of it to start, and nothing here is required to log a workout. Skim for anything that sounds useful, then follow the link to learn how it works. If you are brand new, the <a href="/guides">starting guides</a> are a gentler place to begin.</p>

  <h2>Logging a workout</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Set logging</a></strong> - weight, reps, duration, and distance, with the right fields for each exercise type.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging#set-types">Warm-up and working sets</a></strong> - mark any set as a warm-up so it stays out of your records.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging#rest-timer">Rest timer</a></strong> - starts on its own after a set, with custom durations, sound, and vibration.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging#supersets">Supersets</a></strong> - group exercises you alternate between, with automatic advancing.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/glossary">RPE and RIR</a></strong> - record how hard each set felt, if you want that detail.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Per-set comments</a></strong> - jot a form cue or note an odd rep on a single set.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Repeat last set</a></strong> - copy your previous set in one tap.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Skip a set</a></strong> - mark a planned set as skipped without deleting it.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Workout notes</a></strong> - a comment for the whole session.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/logging">Resume a workout</a></strong> - reopen today's finished session and add more.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings">Hands-free flow</a></strong> - keep the screen on, auto-select the next set, and auto-advance between exercises.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Exercises</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises">Over 360 built-in exercises</a></strong> - across eight categories, including machine, cable, and unilateral variants.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises#search-filter">Search and filter</a></strong> - by name, muscle group, or equipment type.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises#creating">Custom exercises</a></strong> - add anything that is not in the library.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises#types">Exercise types</a></strong> - weight and reps, bodyweight, timed, distance, and combinations.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises">Favorites and avoided</a></strong> - flag the lifts you love and the ones you never want to see.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises">Linked exercises</a></strong> - tie variants together so they share PR history.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises">Custom categories</a></strong> - organize the library your own way.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/exercises">Per-exercise settings</a></strong> - default increment, rest, bar weight, tempo, and notes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Routines and programs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines#creating">Build routines</a></strong> - multi-day programs with set and rep targets per exercise.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines#programs">Built-in programs</a></strong> - StrongLifts 5x5, Starting Strength, GZCLP, 5/3/1 BBB, PPL, Upper/Lower, and Full Body.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines#predefined-sets">Predefined sets</a></strong> - your targets are filled in the moment you start a session.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines#starting">Schedule or rotation</a></strong> - pin days to weekdays, or rotate through them in order for any number of days.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines#starting">Starting weights</a></strong> - pull from your last session or from the routine plan.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines">Exercise alternatives</a></strong> - pre-set swaps for when a machine is taken.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines">Progressive overload</a></strong> - suggests a weight bump after a run of solid sessions.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines">Auto-progress weights</a></strong> - write the heavier loads you hit back into the plan.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/tools#deload">Deload weeks</a></strong> - detect a due-for-lighter week and reduce weights and sets; start or end one manually, or skip a single workout.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines">Routine folders</a></strong> - group related routines together.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/routines">Routine from past workouts</a></strong> - turn sessions you already logged into a reusable routine.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tracking and progress</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress#prs">Personal records</a></strong> - PRs are detected and tracked for you, by rep count.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress#graphs">Progress graphs</a></strong> - estimated 1RM, max weight, and volume over time.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/glossary">Estimated 1RM</a></strong> - calculated from your logged weight and reps.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress">Volume landmarks</a></strong> - sets per muscle group against research-based MEV and MRV zones.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress">Training heatmap</a></strong> - a GitHub-style view of how often you train.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress#muscle-balance">Muscle balance warnings</a></strong> - flags a muscle group that is getting too little work.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/progress#plateau-detection">Plateau detection</a></strong> - spots an exercise that has stopped progressing.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history#per-exercise">Per-exercise history</a></strong> - every session for a single movement in one place.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history#per-exercise">Editable history</a></strong> - fix any past set or piece of equipment after the fact.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Equipment and gyms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms">Multiple gyms</a></strong> - track where each workout happened.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms#machines">Machines and attachments</a></strong> - log the exact equipment you used.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms#machines">Grip types</a></strong> - overhand, underhand, neutral, wide, close, hammer.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms#machines">Per-machine notes</a></strong> - seat heights and setup cues that stick to the machine.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms#machines">Machine-scoped PRs</a></strong> - keep records separate per machine.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms#machines">Weight config</a></strong> - logging unit and step size per machine, including non-uniform stacks.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/gyms">Per-gym plate inventory</a></strong> - the plates a given gym actually has.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Calculators and tools</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/tools">Plate calculator</a></strong> - which plates to load for a target weight, per gym.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/tools#warmup-calc">Warm-up calculator</a></strong> - warm-up sets worked out from your working weight.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/tools">Use this load</a></strong> - write an achievable plate total straight back into the weight field.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>History</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history#views">List and calendar views</a></strong> - browse past workouts either way.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history#filtering">Filter by category</a></strong> - narrow history to one kind of training.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history">Copy a workout</a></strong> - replicate a past session onto today.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history">Log a past workout</a></strong> - backdate a session you forgot to record.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/history">Share as an image</a></strong> - post a workout summary card.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings#importing">Import</a></strong> - bring history from FitNotes, Strong, Hevy, or Stronglifts.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings#export">Export to CSV</a></strong> - your full per-set history as a spreadsheet.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings#data">Backup and restore</a></strong> - a local database snapshot you control.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings#data">Cloud backup</a></strong> - optional automatic backup to your own Google Drive.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings">Share setups</a></strong> - send routines, gyms, and machines to someone as a .badger file.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/phone-migration">Move to a new phone</a></strong> - carry your history across devices.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings">Workout reminders</a></strong> - scheduled notifications based on your training days.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/help/settings">Themes and accent</a></strong> - dark, light, or system, with a custom accent color.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Everything stays on your device. Badger has no account and no required sign-in, and nothing leaves your phone unless you export, share, or turn on cloud backup yourself.</p>
</HelpLayout>
